<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410729>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood phylogeny of Lygodactylus using ND2. Nodes supported by ML and BI are indicated by black dots. nodes only supported by the ML tree are indicated with half-filled black dots. nodes only supported by BI are indicated by half-filled red dots. and nodes with low support in both the ML and BI trees have red dots. Species of Lygodactylus occurring in Angola have a star next to them in the tree. Species within the Madgascan Lygodactylus clade include L. tolampyae, L. heterurus, L. arnoulti. Species in the Greater Drakensberg group include; L. nigropunctatus, L. graniticolus, L. ocellatus, L. soutpansbergensis. L. incognitus, L. montiscaeruli, L. waterbergensis, and L. methueni. Note that this tree should be used only as a guide to shallow relationships in the genus and to indicate relative divergence." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4410729/files/figure.png" .

